From: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2025 18:17:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] ath12k-extn: Add 240MHz minimal extension patch to ath12K

This minimal patch integrates the following code with the main mac80211
component:

1. Update the maximum allowed bandwidth and allow 320MHz operation for
the above mentioned channel freqencies.
2. Receive the vendor NL command - QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_240MHZ_INFO
from hostapd app. Parse the 240MHz STA capability information from this
vendor NL. This vendor NL is sent from hostapd during STA association
at the AP side.
3. Add support to store 240MHz STA capability information in the ahvif
structure as a list. This list contains the 240MHz capability of the
STA, and its mac address obtained by parsing the STA association
request frame during association at the AP side. This information is
used by the mac80211 later to post the 240MHz capability of STA to the fw.
4. Add support to delete this list when the STA information needs to be
cleaned during disassociation/ disconnection.

Signed-off-by: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Venkateswara Swamy Bandaru <vbandaru@qti.qualcomm.com>
